remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoder` provides static methods for encoding images and image sequences to the
WebP format. Single-frame images can be encoded with the `Encode` overloads, while animated
WebP files are produced by the `EncodeAnimated` overloads using a sequence of
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderFrame> instances.

This type has no instance state and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
using var pixmap = bitmap.PeekPixels();
var options = new SKWebpEncoderOptions(SKWebpEncoderCompression.Lossy, 80);
using var data = SKWebpEncoder.Encode(pixmap, options);
File.WriteAllBytes("output.webp", data.ToArray());
```
